China's Anhui Wins Tender to Upgrade Mozambique Airport, Noticias Reports

-- B y   F r e d   K a t e r e r e
-- 
2011-02-21T05:29:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-21/china-s-anhui-wins-tender-to-upgrade-mozambique-airport-noticias-reports.html
  China ’s Anhui Foreign Economic
Construction Group has won a tender to upgrade the domestic wing
of Maputo International Airport, the Noticias newspaper reported
citing  Mozambique ’s Transport and Communication minister Paulo
Zucula.  The facility is expected to cost $36 million and will be
able to handle 580 passengers at peak times, the Maputo-based
daily said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Katerere in Maputo at 
 fkaterere@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Agnes Nikoi at 
 anikoi@bloomberg.net  